Locality: Long Ridge OSP--Peter's Creek Trailhead (SM Co.)
Observation Details: Immature male, continuing bird, first reported from this location by Chris Harwood. Often but not always associated with another bunting, seen often flying together, in one point when seen them in flight, I thought  both looked very alike, there is then possibility that in fact there might be two Indigo Buntings. From gate take obscure unfrequented trail along park border line to the right ( one with no bike sign) go up about 100 meters to closest conifers, bunting/s often flying and singing between those trees and cluster of large oaks a few hundred meters below.
